<br>
These items vastly speed up raids and can be absolutely vital in a win.<br>
<br>
1) For massive mana out put, group a mage, bard and a healer. use Torpor, Celestial heal or similar healing DoT if possible. The mage drops rods for others' use, and uses them to recover more mana back himself, while the healer repairs the mage's injuries. Heal DoT spells can give MORE health back then the mage has, so clicking a rod while the heal DoT is in effect maximizies the heal spells potential.<br>
  Doing this you can fully mana charge a raid in a drastically reduced time.<br>
  Hit point buff the mage (Protection of the Glades or Aegolism) before hand, add clarity2, Gift of Brilliance, Insight.<br>
<br>
2) All healers should have a rod hotkeyed before major fights, ALL HEALERS!! While healers have to beware of low health aggro, it is vital for them to have mana. One click can mean the difference for a CH on the main tank, or the main tank dying and the raid is fubared. if you can heal, have a rod.<br>
<br>
3) Find a good spot to drop rods, tell folk to stay out of this spot so rods can be grabbed easily by those as need.<br>
<br>
4) If you have mana and time, drop rods, get EVERYONE on raid to pick one up, then those who do not need mana drop the rods before engagement/major buffing starts at chosen *rod spot* so casters can go there for mana as need.<br>
<br>
5) Wizard with epic + Rod of Transverange = Death Star <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Their epic's Rune effect prevents all harm from 2 uses of the rod.<br>
<br>
6) if possible have every caster with a rod hotkeyed, one nuke, one rune may make the difference.<br>
<br>
7) Do not turn your nose up at this duty. You can halve the time taken on a raid and prevent a wipeout. It is *IMPORTANT*<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  You can use a rod charge when at full health, thus regaining mana. If you ask for a Regen cast on self, this becomes *extremely* good! This is very useful on raids where you have no pet to worry about and have the time to do this, or if you're very fast on your feet <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Dropping rods in a fight with the Keeper tonight kept the clerics going OOM, think on that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
